casebody.data:
TRUMP RUFFIN COMMERCIAL, LLC, Petitioner v. NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD, Respondent No. 16-1386

September Term, 2016

United States Court of Appeals, District of Columbia Circuit. Filed: 12/29/2016

NLRB-28CA181475

Matthew J. Cute, Assistant General Counsel, The Trump Organization, Rancho Palos Verdes, CA, for Petitioner. Linda Dreeben, Deputy Associate General Counsel, National Labor Relations Board (NLRB), Appellate and Supreme Court Litigation Branch, Washington, DC, for Respondent. Eric Briner Myers, Esquire, Davis, Co-well & Bowe, LLP, San Francisco, CA, for Movants-Intervenors for Respondent.

ORDER

Upon consideration of petitioner’s unopposed motion for voluntary dismissal of the petition for review, it is

ORDERED that the motion be granted and this case be dismissed.

The Clerk is directed to issue the mandate forthwith.
